item.title: AB Foods Lifts Guidance on Robust Sales Growth
item.description: Associated British Foods said it expected adjusted operating profit for fiscal 2023 to be slightly better than previously forecast, with Primark same-store sales growth seen at 9%.

item.title: UK Wages Outpace Inflation, Despite Slowing Jobs Market
item.description: U.K. wage growth held steady in the three months to July at a record level, outstripping inflation and offering the Bank of England further evidence of the persistence of rising wages, even as rising unemployment presents signs of a looser labor market.

item.title: Smurfit Kappa and WestRock Merge
item.description: Smurfit Kappa and WestRock have formally signed a merger agreement, creating a new company worth some $20 billion, with a main listing on the NYSE and a standard listing in London.

item.title: Dollar Trading Seen Quiet Ahead of Wednesday's US CPI Data
item.description: The dollar steadied after edging lower on Monday and ING said trading should be quiet ahead of Wednesday’s U.S. inflation data, adding that it sees risks of a higher-than-expected core print.

item.title: Eurozone Government Bond Supply to Come at Short-End of Curve
item.description: Short-end government bond supply from Germany and Netherlands on Tuesday faces risks from the ECB’s upcoming meeting on Thursday, Citi said.
